AC   P36190;
Ceratotoxin-A precursor 1.
"cDNA sequence and expression of the ceratotoxin gene encoding an
antibacterial sex-specific peptide from the medfly Ceratitis capitata
(diptera).";
"Purification and primary structure of ceratotoxin A and B, two
antibacterial peptides from the female reproductive accessory glands
of the medfly Ceratitis capitata (Insecta:Diptera).";
-!- FUNCTION: Female-specific peptides with potent activity against
    Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria. They have as well
    hemolytic activity.
-!- BIOPHYSICOCHEMICAL PROPERTIES:
    Temperature dependence:
      Thermostable. Still active at 100 degrees Celsius;
-!- SUBUNIT: Homopolymer of four to six subunits.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted protein.
Antibiotic; Antimicrobial; Cytolysis; Direct protein sequencing;
Hemolysis; Immune response; Innate immunity; Signal.
TMZERO
